
[1]vitriolic

   VITRIOL'IC, a. Pertaining to vitriol; having the qualities of vitriol,
   or obtained from vitriol.

   Vitriolic acid, in modern chimistry is denominated sulphuric acid, the
   base of it being sulphur; sulphur completely saturated with oxygen.
